The paper discusses the design and optimization of a 5G software-defined wireless network (5G-SDWN) using multi-layer resource management. This involves the convergence of software-defined networking (SDN), software-defined radio (SDR), and virtualization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the control and data planes, resource management, and quality of experience, which are related to system and control theory (cs.SY), information theory (cs.IT), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper proposes a flexible protocol structure and investigates the effects of joint user-association and resource allocation, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
